New Records: Stephen Curry scored a season-high 36 points, including 17 in the third quarter, and hit two clutch three-pointers with his signature 'night night' celebration in the Warriors' 127-116 victory over the Thunder on November 10, 2024.
Jonathan Kuminga scored 12 points in the second quarter, turning a seven-point deficit into a seven-point lead, and finished with 20 points in the game.
Key Match Events: Stephen Curry's clutch 'night night' three-pointer with 30 seconds left sealed the Warriors' win.
The Warriors came back from a 31-point lead over the Rockets in their previous game but managed to prevent a similar deficit against the Thunder.
Post-Match Reflections: Draymond Green dished out a game-high 11 assists and played a significant role in the Warriors' win.
De'Anthony Melton had his highest-scoring game as a Warrior, finishing with 19 points and 10 rebounds.
Milestones or significant achievements: The Warriors finished a tough road trip with a 4-1 record, including wins over the Boston Celtics and the Thunder.
